This product relies on the following third-party components (invoked as
separate processes or referenced as design/library sources):

- whisper.cpp — MIT License — https://github.com/ggml-org/whisper.cpp
  Used for local speech-to-text. Bundled/built under vendor/.

- FFmpeg — LGPL v2.1+ — https://ffmpeg.org
  Invoked as a subprocess only (no static/dynamic linking, no --enable-gpl).
  License remains LGPL; no GPL components are enabled.

- llama.cpp — MIT License — https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
  Used (experimental) for the local natural-language planner. Built under
  vendor/; invoked as a subprocess / local server.

- Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct — Apache License 2.0 —
  https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct
  Default planner model (experimental). Downloaded on demand by the user via
  setup-llm.sh; not bundled. (The non-Apache 3B variant is intentionally not used.)

- @napi-rs/canvas — MIT License — https://github.com/Brooooooklyn/canvas
  Used to rasterize subtitles/overlays headlessly.

- OpenCut — MIT License — https://github.com/OpenCut-app/OpenCut
  Referenced for design/architecture; any borrowed code retains MIT notice.

GPL-licensed editors (Kdenlive, Shotcut, OpenShot) are NOT used as code
sources — referenced for UX only.

Demo & test assets
------------------
The sample photos used only to exercise the image-overlay pipeline
(demo/photo1.jpg, demo/photo2.jpg, and any demo renders derived from them
under demo-output/) are fetched from Lorem Picsum (https://picsum.photos,
seeds dawncut1 / dawncut2), which serves photos under the Unsplash License
(https://unsplash.com/license) — free to use, including redistribution, with
attribution appreciated. These are test fixtures only and are regenerable with
`pnpm demo:assets`; the script falls back to self-generated CC0 color cards
when offline. No third-party photo is required for dawn-cut to build or run.

## Bundled binaries (issue #19, 2026-06-11)
- ffmpeg / ffprobe (Resources/bin): built from FFmpeg n7.1 source with
  `--disable-gpl --disable-nonfree` (LGPL v2.1+ core only, no external GPL
  libraries; H.264 encoding via Apple VideoToolbox). Build script:
  scripts/build-ffmpeg-lgpl.sh. FFmpeg source: https://ffmpeg.org
- whisper-cli (Resources/bin): whisper.cpp (MIT), static build
  (BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=OFF). https://github.com/ggml-org/whisper.cpp
- The whisper model (ggml-large-v3-turbo) is downloaded on first use from
  Hugging Face (ggerganov/whisper.cpp) into the user data directory; it is
  not distributed inside the app bundle.
